I am a librarian. I love my job. I am not very interested in books. I enjoy fantasy. I like animals. I take a ferry to work. I like being on the water. I grew up by the ocean. I miss the ocean. My kids come to the library to get books. I have kids. I sometimes work with polar bears. I work at a zoo. I am afraid of polar bears. I enjoy my job. My favorite thing is taking care of baby penguins. I work with penguins. Penguins are one of my favorite animals. I can get free tickets to the zoo.,"I love it! So many people come in looking for just the right book and it is my favorite thing to see a happy person walking out the door ready to start a literary journey! I have a hard time getting into books, what would you recommend as a genre for someone like me?  I have to take the ferry. It may be a little time consuming but it is so much fun to be out on the water everyday~ I bet, I grew up by the ocean and I miss it very much. Do your kids visit you at the library? Very much so, I work with penguins mostly. Sometimes I get to help with the polar bears, but they are quite frightening. I'd have to say my favorite part of the day is taking care of the baby penguins. They are one of my favorites, and they're lots of fun to watch while they play. I can get free tickets if you'd like to bring the kids to meet them.",test_792_2
