I am not a Jets fan. I am moving to New York. I will go to school in New York. I am thinking about going to NYU. I want to major in Linguistics. I want to go to University of Chicago. I dont know if ill study mechanical or electrical engineering. I want to major in engineering. I love building things. I am fascinated by mechanics and how everyday things work. I'm fascinated with engineering. I have built an engine and several radios. I know sign language. I have a deaf friend. I want to study the difference between spoken and signed languages. I want to travel and learn in different countries.,"I have decided I will be attending school when I move to New York. But I will not be rooting for the Jets. I think both decisions are good. LOL. What school will you attend? I am thinking about going to NYU, what college are you thinking about going to? My first choice is actually University of Chicago. I want to major in Linguistics and they have a great program.  How about you? do you know what you will major in?  I think that I am going to major in Engineering. I am leaning towards either mechanical or electrical. I love building things, and I am fascinated by the mechanics on how everyday things work. I have built a small, basic 2-stroke engine, and several radios. What kind of things are you looking to do with the Linguistics degree that you are going to go to school for? I have a deaf friend and I've learn sign language. I want to study the difference between spoken and signed languages. I don't even know what to do with the degree. Except get more degrees until I become a professor. I like that idea. I hope that in undergrad I will get to travel and learn about sign languages in different countries. ",test_857_2
